value.text: all the waiters and waitresses was doubting me as a customer

data.text: food was great but very devastated by the service. i was there eating alone but all the waiters and waitresses was doubting me as a customer. however, as i sat down to my table, all of a sudden pops out a security guard near the cashier.bneedless to say, i was wearing pretty much causal clothes and shoes, but still i dont feel comfortable at all eating with waiter, manager and security looking at me the whole time. the waitress that served me was speaking at a sarcastic way everytime i wanted to order. this was actually like my 3rd time eating there(pvj outlet). really though, everytime i wanted to take buffet, the security was all eyes on me. the funny thing is, i saw a lady eating alone but she didnt get the “treatment” i received. as i wanted to pay at the cashier, the security was stanby behind me as if i was going to be arrested. as soon as my card was approved on the machine, the waitress all gave a nod to each other and to the security as if i was safe to go. cant believe that this kinda stupid thing still exist.
